  "text": "Kashiwagi et al [CITATION_1] and Yanai et al [CITATION_2] reported three mutations responsible for CD36 deficiency, a substitution of T for C at nt 478 of CD36 cDNA, a dinucleotide deletion at nt 539, 17 18 and a single nucleotide insertion at nt 1159. 17 19 The substitution of T for C at 478 leads directly to CD36 deficiency via defects in post-translational modification. [CITATION_3] The dinucleotide deletion at nt 539 or the single nucleotide insertion at nt 1159 caused a frameshift leading to the appearance of a translation stop codon and a marked reduction in the level of CD36 mRNA. 18 19 Furthermore, the dinucleotide deletion at nt 539 may affect the splicing of exon 4.",
